============================================================
SYSTEM REQUIREMENTS DOCUMENT (SRD)
Golden Governor v125 Light – Solana Playground Edition
Level A Safety-Critical Requirements
============================================================

1. INTRODUCTION
------------------------------------------------------------
1.1 Purpose
This System Requirements Document (SRD) defines all functional,
safety, integrity, timing, oracle, and operational requirements for
the Golden Governor v125 Light program deployed on Solana Devnet.

1.2 Scope
Golden Governor v125 Light is an on-chain safety governor that
enforces deterministic constraints on leverage, exposure, drawdown,
oracle integrity, MEV detection, and temporal sequencing for a
trading strategy. It operates as a safety kernel and gatekeeper.

1.3 Assurance Level
This SRD is written to Level A rigor (NASA-style), meaning:
- No single failure may lead to uncontrolled behavior.
- All requirements are testable, traceable, and deterministic.
- All safety-critical logic must be explicitly defined.

1.4 Definitions
- Governor: The on-chain state machine enforcing safety.
- Authority: The signer controlling this governor instance.
- PDA: Program Derived Address storing governor state.
- Mode: Operational state (Normal, Degraded, Recovering, Lockout).
- Integrity Hash: Zero-trust state validation checksum.

============================================================
2. SYSTEM OVERVIEW
------------------------------------------------------------
The system consists of:
- A single Anchor program (golden_governor)
- A PDA storing GoldenGovernor state
- Oracle inputs from two independent feeds
- A zero-trust integrity verification subsystem
- A mode-based safety envelope
- A watchdog subsystem for anomaly detection

============================================================
3. FUNCTIONAL REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------

3.1 Initialization Requirements
--------------------------------
GG-REQ-001:
The system SHALL create a GoldenGovernor PDA using seeds:
[b"governor", authority_pubkey].

GG-REQ-002:
The system SHALL initialize all state fields to valid defaults,
including:
- mode = Normal
- peak_equity = initial_equity
- current_drawdown = 0
- integrity_salt = current slot

GG-REQ-003:
The system SHALL enforce:
max_drawdown_bps ≤ MAX_DRAWDOWN_BPS_MAX.

GG-REQ-004:
If max_drawdown_bps > DEFAULT_MAX_DRAWDOWN_BPS,
the system SHALL clamp it to DEFAULT_MAX_DRAWDOWN_BPS.

GG-REQ-005:
The system SHALL compute and store an integrity_hash after initialization.

3.2 Trade Execution Requirements
--------------------------------
GG-REQ-010:
The system SHALL verify zero-trust integrity via zt_lite_verify
before processing a trade.

GG-REQ-011:
The system SHALL load two oracle prices and validate:
- feed pubkeys match expected
- data age ≤ MAXIMUM_AGE
- price ≥ 0

GG-REQ-012:
The system SHALL compute cross-feed difference in basis points and
REJECT the trade if:
diff_bps > CROSS_CHECK_MAX_DIFF_BPS.

GG-REQ-013:
The system SHALL compute MEV spike detection and REJECT the trade if:
price_change_bps > MEV_MAX_PRICE_CHANGE_BPS.

GG-REQ-014:
The system SHALL compute friction bound:
expected_spread * 1.618
and REJECT the trade if slippage exceeds this bound.

GG-REQ-015:
The system SHALL enforce:
leverage_used ≤ max_leverage.

GG-REQ-016:
The system SHALL enforce:
new_equity ≤ max_exposure.

GG-REQ-017:
The system SHALL update:
- current_equity
- peak_equity (if increased)
- current_drawdown
- mode (Normal/Degraded/Recovering/Lockout)
- last_price
- last_action_slot
- last_sense_timestamp

GG-REQ-018:
If drawdown_bps ≥ max_drawdown_bps,
the system SHALL enter Lockout mode.

3.3 Risk Tick Requirements
---------------------------
GG-REQ-030:
The system SHALL enforce slot-based rate limiting:
current_slot ≥ last_risk_tick_slot + MIN_SLOTS_BETWEEN_RISK_TICKS.

GG-REQ-031:
The system SHALL recompute drawdown and update mode accordingly.

GG-REQ-032:
The system SHALL update:
- last_risk_tick_slot
- last_action_slot
- last_sense_timestamp
- integrity_hash

3.4 Watchdog Tick Requirements
-------------------------------
GG-REQ-040:
The system SHALL enforce slot-based rate limiting identical to risk_tick.

GG-REQ-041:
The system SHALL increment watchdog_nonce and REJECT if:
new_nonce ≤ old_nonce.

GG-REQ-042:
The system SHALL compute oracle move in basis points and enter Lockout if:
percent_move > 2000 bps.

GG-REQ-043:
The system SHALL recompute integrity_hash and enter Lockout if:
computed_hash ≠ stored_hash AND stored_hash ≠ 0.

3.5 Withdrawal Requirements
----------------------------
GG-REQ-050:
The system SHALL enforce withdrawal lock:
current_time - init_timestamp ≥ WITHDRAWAL_LOCK_SECONDS.

GG-REQ-051:
The system SHALL allow withdrawals ONLY in Normal mode.

GG-REQ-052:
The system SHALL enforce:
amount ≤ current_equity.

GG-REQ-053:
The system SHALL update:
- current_equity
- last_action_slot
- integrity_hash

3.6 Phoenix Restart Requirements
---------------------------------
GG-REQ-060:
The system SHALL allow phoenix_restart ONLY in Lockout mode.

GG-REQ-061:
The system SHALL enforce cooldown:
current_time - lockout_timestamp ≥ PHOENIX_COOLDOWN_SECONDS.

GG-REQ-062:
The system SHALL transition to Recovering mode and reset:
- current_drawdown = 0
- peak_equity = current_equity

GG-REQ-063:
The system SHALL update integrity_hash.

3.7 Policy Upgrade Requirements
--------------------------------
GG-REQ-070:
The system SHALL require zero-trust verification with allow_lockout = true.

GG-REQ-071:
The system SHALL enforce:
new_version > current policy_version.

GG-REQ-072:
The system SHALL update:
- policy_version
- integrity_hash

============================================================
4. SAFETY REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------

4.1 Oracle Safety
------------------
GG-SAF-001:
The system SHALL reject any oracle feed whose pubkey does not match
the expected feed ID.

GG-SAF-002:
The system SHALL reject any oracle update older than MAXIMUM_AGE.

GG-SAF-003:
The system SHALL reject any oracle price < 0.

4.2 MEV and Market Safety
--------------------------
GG-SAF-010:
The system SHALL reject trades if price movement exceeds
MEV_MAX_PRICE_CHANGE_BPS.

GG-SAF-011:
The system SHALL reject trades if slippage exceeds:
expected_spread * 1.618.

4.3 Drawdown Safety
--------------------
GG-SAF-020:
The system SHALL compute drawdown as:
(peak_equity - current_equity) / peak_equity * 10,000.

GG-SAF-021:
The system SHALL enter Lockout if:
drawdown_bps ≥ max_drawdown_bps.

4.4 Integrity Safety
---------------------
GG-SAF-030:
The system SHALL compute integrity_hash after every state change.

GG-SAF-031:
The system SHALL reject operations if:
computed_hash ≠ stored_hash AND stored_hash ≠ 0.

GG-SAF-032:
The system SHALL enter Lockout if watchdog detects integrity mismatch.

4.5 Temporal Safety
--------------------
GG-SAF-040:
The system SHALL reject operations if:
elapsed_time > 3 seconds (SafetyKernelTimeout).

GG-SAF-041:
The system SHALL enforce slot-based rate limits for:
- risk_tick
- watchdog_tick

============================================================
5. PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------

GG-PERF-001:
All instructions SHALL complete within Solana’s compute budget.

GG-PERF-002:
All integrity checks SHALL use constant-time or near-constant-time
operations to avoid timing side channels.

GG-PERF-003:
All arithmetic SHALL use checked math to prevent overflow.

============================================================
6. RELIABILITY REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------

GG-REL-001:
No single oracle failure SHALL cause unsafe behavior.

GG-REL-002:
No single state mutation SHALL bypass integrity_hash verification.

GG-REL-003:
Lockout mode SHALL halt all operations except:
- phoenix_restart
- upgrade_policy (with allow_lockout)

============================================================
7. EVENT AND TELEMETRY REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------

GG-EVT-001:
The system SHALL emit GovernorStateChanged on:
- mode change
- equity change
- drawdown change
- integrity_hash update

GG-EVT-002:
The system SHALL emit EnvelopeViolation on:
- oracle cross-check failure
- MEV spike
- integrity mismatch
- lockout triggers

============================================================
8. VERIFICATION REQUIREMENTS
------------------------------------------------------------

GG-VRF-001:
Each requirement SHALL be verifiable via:
- direct code inspection
- unit tests
- integration tests
- event inspection
- simulated oracle inputs

GG-VRF-002:
Each requirement SHALL map to at least one test case in the
Traceability Matrix.

